CMakeList:
 In order to add new files (.cu or .cpp) to the code, it must be included their names in the corresponding sections(CUDA_FILES and CPP_FILES).

	Important:
	If it is used templates in some file, you CANNOT include this file in the CMakelist otherwise you will obtain a duplicate definition error. Also, if you split the implementation(.h or .hpp) from the definition(.cu or .cpp) you must include in the main file the .cu or cpp directly instead of include the .h or .hpp.


MakeFile:
	For compiling, running and checking the code, you need to open the Terminal in the IonWake folder and write the word make from the Terminal  and selecting one of the options below.

	Makefile options:
	
		build_debug: function to build the code in debug mode(slower but more detailed)
		build_release: function to build the code in release mode(faster but less detailed)	
		clean: function to remove the build directory
		run: function to run the code
		status: check the status of a job
		info: get errors and extra informations of the job


Input Files
	_params.txt
		Contains general input parameters for the simulation. Such as the timestep length
		and the radius of the dust particles.
	dust_params.txt
		Contains the initial positions and charges for the dust particles. 
	_timestep.txt
		Is used to turn on and off several time step options.

Timestep Options
	TR-ion-pos
		Prints a trace of an ion's position to the trace output file.
	TR-ion-vel
		Prints a trace of an ion's velocity to the trace output file.
	TR-ion-acc
		Prints a trace of an ion's acceleration to the trace output file.
	CH-charge-dust
		Allows the dust charge to be dynamicaly calculated.
	CH-move-dust
		Allows the dust position, velocity, and acceleration to be 
		dynamically calculated.
 
Sample parameter values from params.txt
	NUM_ION   		   60000 //number of ions
    DEN_FAR_PLASMA     1e14  //background plasma density
    TEMP_ELC   		   29011 //temperature in Kelvin
    TEMP_ION   		   290   //temperature in Kelvin
    DEN_DUST   		   1510  // density of dust material kg/m^3
    MASS_SINGLE_ION    6.633521e-26
    MACH   	  		   1.00  // drift vel of ions relative to sound speed
    SOFT_RAD   		   1e-6  // softening radius for ion-ion forces
    RAD_DUST   		   5e-6  // radius of dust grains
    CHARGE_SINGLE_ION -1     // charge in units of e
    TIME_STEP   	   1.0e-8 //time step in seconds
    NUM_TIME_STEP      200000
    GEOMETRY	 	   0 	// 0 = sphere, 1 = cylinder
    RAD_SIM_DEBYE      1.5 	// radius of spherical simulation region (debye)
    NUM_VEL_DIV   	   50 	//for calculating incoming ion velocity
    NUM_QTH_DIV   	   100 // angles for incoming ion pos: 3 for cylinder, 100 
    RAD_CYL_DEBYE	   2.0	// radius of cylindrical sim bounds (debye)
    HT_CYL_DEBYE	   5.0	// half the height of cylinder (in debye lengths)
    P10X	 		  -3.3064e5 // coefficient for exterior ion force: cylinder
    P12X   			  -1.7962e9 
    P14X	 		   1.6279e14
    P01Z   			  -1917.3
   	P21Z	 		  -2.4581e9 	
  	P03Z			  -3.4150e8 
 	P23Z	 		   3.7472e14
 	P05Z	  		  -9.8550e13
	PRESSURE		  100	// pressure in Torr
	FREQ			  500	// frequency of AC E-field switching
	E_FIELD			  350	// magnitude of AC Efield (V/m)
	DUST_CONFINEMENT  2.63e6 // radial confining force for dust
